We have started to use the School News app by Edlio. It’s a simple way to view the school’s news feeds and calendars, and also receive push notifications directly from us.

It’s FREE to download to your iOS or Android phone and quick to set up:

Go to the App Store or Google Play and search for “School News by Edlio” to install.
Open the app and search for Tekoa Academy of Accelerated Studies; tap “Add School.”
Enable push notification by going to the Alerts tab and tapping “Enable Notifications.”

All of the news and events posted to our website are posted here for easy access. You can also add multiple Edlio-powered schools and/or districts to gather all news, events, and alerts in this one app. We’ll send push notifications out to keep you updated on urgent news.

Click the link below for instructions...

Due to Governor Abbott’s announcement that schools will remain closed, we will be postponing the return to school until May 4. The Continuity Instructional Plan will continue until that time. Tekoa Academy of Accelerated Studies will continue to communicate with parents to make sure you are informed about important dates. We want to encourage everyone to review the daily assignments for students on www.TekoaCharterSchool.org under the "Learn @ Home" banner.

We will continue to monitor this situation and provide opportunities to access student work and meals. Tekoa Academy will maintain contact with parents, students, and faculty through callout, website, and Facebook. Once again, we want to encourage everyone to follow all social distancing guidelines put forth by our local and national leaders.

TEKOA ACADEMY EXTENDS CLOSURE UNTIL APRIL 3

Given the rapidly evolving situation with COVID-19, Tekoa Academy of Accelerated Studies will extend the suspension of normal district operations through Friday, April 3rd in an effort to support our nation’s need to slow the spread of the novel coronavirus, or COVID-19. Our health officials report that cases are continuing to spread in the state, and an increase in confirmed cases in our country seems likely. Suspending operations for this length of time will allow us to determine, in coordination with local health officials, whether the virus is continuing to have community spread or whether it has been contained.

Read more here:
https://4.files.edl.io/091a/03/20/20/161757-0f317cd5-3569-4aa3-840e-87dab136fe43.pdf

post_text:
Tekoa Academy of Accelerated Studies STEM School is committed to maintaining a safe and healthy environment for our students and employees. As such, we are closely monitoring the ongoing COVID-19 coronavirus outbreak according to the guidelines and recommendations of the CDC (Centers for Disease Control and Prevention). We want to share with you the actions we are taking to help protect our employees and students.

We’ve advised our students, families, and employees to follow the public health authorities' guidance regarding hygiene and personal travel, and we’ve reinforced existing Tekoa Academy policy encouraging employees who exhibit flu-like symptoms to stay home and consult with a medical professional. We’ve limited business travel and encouraged colleagues to leverage technology to hold business meetings whenever possible.

Tekoa Academy is committed to providing a healthy and safe learning environment to our students.

We will continue to keep you informed of any urgent changes or cancellations.

Tekoa Academy of Accelerated Studies STEM School is committed to maintaining a safe and healthy environment for our students and employees. As such, we are closely monitoring the ongoing COVID-19 coronavirus outbreak according to the guidelines and recommendations of the CDC (Centers for Disease Control and Prevention). We want to share with you the actions we are taking to help protect our employees and students.

We’ve advised our students, families, and employees to follow the public health authorities' guidance regarding hygiene and personal travel, and we’ve reinforced existing Tekoa Academy policy encouraging employees who exhibit flu-like symptoms to stay home and consult with a medical professional. We’ve limited business travel and encouraged colleagues to leverage technology to hold business meetings whenever possible.

Tekoa Academy is committed to providing a healthy and safe learning environment to our students.

We will continue to keep you informed of any urgent changes or cancellations.
